<HEADLINE>
<P>
'LAKE OF FIRE' LYRICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * In response to Bob Guccione Jr.'s article concerning the death of singer 
Kurt Cobain (Commentary, April 15): The lyrics attributed to Cobain as "a 
twisted version of his own eulogy" were in fact written by Curt Kirkwood of the 
Meat Puppets, whose song "Lake of Fire" Cobain performed with Kirkwood on the 
MTV "Unplugged" concert referred to in the article. Cobain's suicide is 
nonetheless tragic, but let's give credit where credit is due. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM SHINBROT 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
