<HEADLINE>
<P>
GATT TRADE PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Is anyone minding the store? It seems GATT is working to create a World 
Trade Organization. Imagine! A permanent bureaucracy that would have power over 
U.S. laws, yet be unaccountable, secretive and undemocratic.Under the WTO, 
panels of three unelected trade bureaucrats would hear challenges by other 
nations to U.S. laws. If a challenged U.S. law was found to violate its trade 
rules, the WTO could direct the United States to change the law or face 
automatic economic sanctions. This would put laws passed by Congress and state 
and local governments at risk to unelected, unaccountable trade bureaucrats. 
The process is closed to the press and public. Documents are kept secret and 
are not subject to the U.S. Freedom of Information Act. 
</P>
<P>
 The World Trade Organization is wrong for a democracy like ours. Where are our 
representatives? 
</P>
<P>
 HELEN TIEGER 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
