<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cincinnati Reds put catcher Joe Oliver on the 15-day disabled list because 
of a swollen ankle and traded minor leaguers Ross Powell and Marty Lister to 
the Houston Astros for catcher Eddie Taubensee. . . . Marge Schott, owner of 
the Reds, can expect to be cited for violating city law if she smokes in areas 
of Riverfront Stadium where smoking is prohibited, City Council members said. 
She did not challenge the law during Tuesday's game against the Pittsburgh 
Pirates. . . . George Steinbrenner, owner of the New York Yankees, was released 
from a Tampa, Fla., hospital after an overnight stay for an undisclosed reason. 
