<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: WHAT'S UP? DOCK WILL BE CLOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some might say the decision to close the Silverwood Lake dock to fishing is, 
well, a crappie one.Lake management says it is a necessary one. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were getting 50-60 people, even on weekdays, fishing for crappie," marina 
supervisor Kevin Howard said. "People were tripping over each other and hooking 
each other." 
</P>
<P>
 But the last straw, Howard said, was when a smoker carelessly flicked a 
lighted cigarette last Thursday, setting fire to the dock. "That's when 
management said, 'No more crappie fishing,' " Howard said. The dock will remain 
closed to fishing indefinitely. 
</P>
