<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; MAGGIORA FOLLOWS IN BROTHER'S FOOTSTEPS WITH NO-HITTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saugus High senior John Maggiora faced two batters over the minimum while 
pitching a no-hitter in a 7-0 victory over Burroughs in a Foothill League game 
Tuesday at Burroughs. 
</P>
<P>
 The no-hitter is the first for Saugus (12-4-1, 4-1 in league play) since 
Maggiora's brother, Doug, pitched one in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Maggiora struck out three and walked none. He hit a batter in the sixth and 
Saugus committed an error in the seventh. VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake def. Loyola, 12-15, 15-13, 16-14, 15-8 -- Harvard, ranked 
second in Southern Section Division I, defeated top-ranked Loyola, in a Mission 
League match. Matt Sebree had 29 kills for the Wolverines (11-1) and Seth 
Rodsky added 22. Court Young had 60 assists. The victory avenged Harvard's 
earlier loss to the Cubs (12-1). Both teams are 8-1 in league play. SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 1, Royal 0 -- Sara Griffin pitched a perfect game, leading Simi 
Valley (12-1, 6-1) in a Marmonte League game at Rancho Simi Park. Griffin, who 
struck out 12, has pitched one other no-hitter and eight shutouts this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicole Newhart singled to score Jenny Conmay in the fourth. COLLEGE BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 8, CS Dominguez Hills 7 -- The Mustangs (12-26-2), an NAIA team, 
upset the NCAA's No. 2-ranked Division II team at Master's. Mark Vail (three 
RBIs) and Kenya Hunt each had two hits, including home runs. Matt Henzie was 
four for four and David Scott three for three to pace a 15-hit attack. The 
Toros (30-12) scored four runs in the eighth. HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Littlerock 7, Quartz Hill 6 -- James Jefferson's two-run triple led a comeback 
for the Lobos, who scored three runs in the seventh inning of a Golden League 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 4, Santa Paula 3 -- Travis Ehrlich's two-run double in the fourth 
lifted the Musketeers in a Frontier League game. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real 2, Kennedy 1 -- Left-hander Randy Wolf (6-1) struck out eight 
and walked none for El Camino Real (12-4, 4-3) in a Northwest Valley Conference 
game. He also doubled and singled. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 3, Burbank 2 -- Freshman left-hander Bobby Graves recorded the final out 
on a ground ball with the tying run on base to preserve the victory for Hart 
(13-4, 5-0). Eric Spindt (4-3) pitched the first 6 2/3 innings, striking out 
two while walking none. 
</P>
