ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dolores Tuimoloau 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Channel Islands 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Track and field 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Tuimoloau won the shot put at 45 feet 6 inches in Rio Mesa 
High's Spartan Relays and set a region record of 46-11 1/2 in the Ventura 
Relays. She threw the discus a Ventura County record 145-0 in the Santa Barbara 
Easter Relays two weeks later.Her only loss of the season in the shot came in 
the Arcadia Invitational but she had a region record and state-leading throw of 
47-0 1/4 Saturday at the Mt. San Antonio College Relays. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Although she avenged her Arcadia loss to Gina Heads of 
Newport Harbor at Mt. SAC, Tuimoloau said that wasn't a priority. "Gina and I 
have been going against each other since we were freshmen, so (losing to her) 
wasn't that big a deal," Tuimoloau said. "But I wanted to throw 50 feet. It's a 
little disappointing not to, but at the same time I (set a personal best), so I 
can't be too upset." 
</P>
