<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS : NOMINEES SOUGHT FOR JOB TRAINING COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Job Training Policy Council of Ventura County, a nonprofit corporation 
that administers job training and placement programs for unemployed workers, is 
seeking nominations for four openings on the council. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members make decisions on the allocation of federal funds and oversee 
operation of programs that use the money. 
</P>
<P>
 This year, the council is responsible for more than $10 million in federal 
funds, corporation officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Board of Supervisors will select the four council members 
from among the nominees, who should be private-sector business leaders, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 To nominate an individual or for information on the job training council, call 
Aram Saroyan at 981-8765. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
