<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; GUTIERREZ'S GRAND SLAM HELPS CANYON KNOCK OFF ORANGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Josh Gutierrez hit a grand slam and run-scoring single to pace Canyon to a 6-3 
Century League baseball victory over visiting Orange Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gutierrez, filling in at first base for the injured Todd Wyatt, gave the 
Comanches a 4-0 lead in the first inning with his home run.Darren Chandler and 
Casey Wilson walked and Eric Valent singled to load the bases with no outs when 
Gutierrez came to bat. 
</P>
<P>
 Gutierrez, who fractured a finger while catching in the first inning in 
Canyon's 15-14 loss to Orange on March 22 and missed two weeks, singled in 
Valent in the third to give Canyon a 5-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange (11-7, 4-4 in league) scored two in the fourth on a double by Sean 
Simpson, an infield single by Marshall Maresh and Eric Mendoza's single.  
</P>
<P>
 Canyon (13-4, 6-1) added a run in the sixth when Wilson doubled home Scott 
Redfox. Art Bell scored for Orange on a balk in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Gunner Strunz (4-2) picked up the victory despite allowing at least one runner 
in each inning. MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
