<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MINICI'S HOMER IN NINTH SPARKS RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Minici hit a three-run home run with two outs in the ninth to give host 
Rancho Santiago a 6-5 victory over Fullerton in an Orange Empire Conference 
baseball game Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (16-15-1, 7-10 in conference) scored three runs in the eighth, 
helped by three errors, to take a 5-2 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Daryle Ward's RBI double with two outs in the ninth cut Fullerton's lead to 
5-3, bringing Minici up to the plate. 
</P>
<P>
 Minici's home run came off Fullerton's Brian Tokarse, who gave up a three-run 
home run to Nick Valencia in the ninth as OCC beat Fullerton, 8-7, Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago (27-9, 10-7) plays Fullerton again at 2:30 p.m. Thursday at 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 In other conference games: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 7, Cypress 5 -- Wade Jackson hit a three-run home in the eighth 
inning to give visiting Saddleback (20-10-1, 10-7) a 7-2 lead. Dennis Cring 
allowed four runs, two earned, and 12 hits in eight-plus innings for the 
victory. Craig Ainsworth pitched the ninth for his fourth save. 
</P>
<P>
 Andy Gonzales had four hits, including a double, and drove in two runs for 
Cypress (26-10, 12-5), which travels to Saddleback Thursday for a 2:30 p.m. 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 4, Golden West 3 (10) -- First-place Riverside (26-7, 13-4) moved 
one game in front of Cypress with the victory. 
</P>
