<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; GARRETT 
MORRIS HOSPITALIZED 3 WEEKS AFTER BEING SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Comedian Garrett Morris was back in the hospital Tuesday after a 3-week-old 
gunshot wound apparently became infected, his publicist said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morris walked into Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital on Monday night 
complaining of pain in his back, publicist Rita Tateel said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "There have been some complications and we don't know what kind of procedure 
will be done," she said. "There is some speculation that he has had some 
inflammation and infection in the area where the bullet was." 
</P>
<P>
 Morris was wounded once in the chest and once in the arm during a botched 
holdup in South-Central Los Angeles. He told the two robbers he had no money. 
</P>
<P>
 The 57-year-old actor was a member of the original cast of "Saturday Night 
Live" in the 1970s, and plays Stan in the current TV comedy "Martin." 
</P>
</TEXT>
