<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; POLICE SEEK WITNESSES IN PEDESTRIAN'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police were seeking witnesses Tuesday to a traffic accident on Olive Avenue 
where an 82-year-old Burbank woman crossing the street was struck and killed by 
a van. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have no witnesses wh came forward," said Burbank Police Detective Richard 
Bison. 
</P>
<P>
 Georgiana Hutchinson, 82, of Burbank was pronounced dead at the scene by 
Burbank Fire Department paramedics after the 10:52 a.m. accident. Bison said 
the woman had been crossing Olive Avenue northbound at Beachwood Drive in an 
unmarked crosswalk when she was struck by a van driven by Anthony Ivancich, 51, 
of Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 No charges have been filed against Ivancich, who had been driving east on 
Olive Avenue just after turning off of Verdugo Avenue when the accident 
happened, Bison said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The questions are: 'Was she legally and safely in the intersection?' and 'If 
she was, then why didn't he yield to her?' " Bison said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bison said Ivancich was questioned at the scene and not taken into custody. 
</P>
<P>
 Police diverted traffic off Olive Avenue between Verdugo and Virginia avenues 
near the Izay Park until about 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Bison asked that any witnesses to the accident, which occurred in front of 
Genio's Restaurant, call him at 818-953-8650. ED BOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
