<TEXT>
<P>
 Saba Petroleum Co.: The oil company has agreed to purchase an oil refinery and 
a 372-acre tract in the Santa Maria Valley area of Santa Barbara County from 
Conoco Inc., the companies said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Saba will use the tract to turn heavy crude oil into asphalt and other lighter 
byproducts, said Saba President Ilyas Chaudhary. Saba will use equity capital 
and borrowings to finance the acquisition. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine-based Saba, an independent oil and gas production company, has field 
offices in Midland, Tex., and Saticoy, Calif. 
</P>
