<TEXT>
<P>
 Diceon Electronics Inc.: The Irvine manufacturer of circuit boards and 
backpanels recorded a loss of $582,000, or 11 cents a share, for its latest 
fiscal quarter, compared to a loss of $8.4 million, or $1.63 a share, for the 
corresponding period a year earlier.Sales for the company's second quarter, 
which ended April 2, were up 12% to $26.2 million from $23.3 million. For the 
first half, the company posted a loss of $3.9 million, or 77 cents a share, 
compared to a loss of $10 million, or $1.95 a share, for the same period a year 
earlier. Six-month sales were $50.5 million, down from $52.1 million. 
</P>
