<TEXT>
<P>
 MAI Systems Corp.: The Irvine computer manufacturer, which emerged from 
bankruptcy protection Jan. 27, reported a 1993 profit of $145.5 million, 
including a one-time gain of $117.3 million from its reorganization.That 
compared to a loss of $182 million for 1992. Revenue fell 59% to $115.3 million 
from $279.4 million. For the fourth quarter, the company said profit totaled 
$59.4 million, including a reorganization gain of $60.4 million. That compared 
to a loss of $92.8 million for the same period a year earlier, when the company 
had a restructuring charge of $68.8 million. Three-month revenue declined 72% 
to $18.1 million from $63.8 million. 
</P>
