<HEADLINE>
<P>
BECKLEY, HUDSON, SIMON TO PLAY IN ALL-STAR BASKETBALL GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mater Dei's Miles Simon, a two-time Times Orange County boys' basketball 
player of the year, and Colleen Hudson and Sarah Beckley, members of 
Brea-Olinda's undefeated Division III State championship girls' team, are among 
a talented group of players in the 29th Orange County boys' and girls' all-star 
basketball games Saturday at Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
 The girls play at 4 p.m. and the boys at 7:30, with the gymnasium being 
cleared between games. Admission is $8 for adults, $5 for children 12 and 
under. 
</P>
<P>
 The games, sponsored by the Costa Mesa Kiwanis Club, will feature some of the 
county's top seniors, with a two-player limit from each team. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda's Nicole Erickson, The Times' girls' player of the year the last 
two seasons, already has committed to participating in two other all-star 
contests -- the maximum allowed each player. 
</P>
<P>
 Teams were selected by coaches with input from various reporters. 
</P>
<P>
 The rosters: 
</P>
<P>
 BOYS 
</P>
<P>
 North -- Greg Abbott (Troy), Scott Davis (Loara), Gil Gonzales (Orange), Frank 
Henderson (Magnolia), Tim Lin (Los Alamitos), Tyler Ream (Whittier Christian), 
Nick Roditis (Katella), Miles Simon (Mater Dei), Ryan Staniec (Los Alamitos), 
Jon Surface (Pacifica), Mike Thimgan (Esperanza), Chris Vlasic (Pacifica). 
Coach: Mike Murphy (Sonora). 
</P>
<P>
 South -- Ali Amiri (University), Ramin Bastani (Corona del Mar), Chris 
Bradshaw (Saddleback), Brad Finneran (Santa Margarita), Brian Finneran (Santa 
Margarita), Tony Gonzalez (Huntington Beach), Thomas Harmon (Century), Ryan 
Karnoff (Trabuco Hills), Micah Kroeger (Edison), Brandon Leimbach (Fountain 
Valley), Luke Mannix (San Clemente), Demitrius Zeigler (University). Coach: 
Gordon Billingsley (Fountain Valley). 
</P>
<P>
 GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 North -- Sarah Beckley (Brea-Olinda), Adrienne Botana (Mater Dei), Chris 
Carrillo (Katella), Jennifer Chey (Rosary), Jessica Eggleston (Cypress), Susan 
Flaming (Cypress), Colleen Hudson (Brea-Olinda), Michol Murray (Garden Grove), 
Leticia Oseguera (Mater Dei), Akilah Rodgers (Rancho Alamitos), Jamie Shine (El 
Modena), Maureen Skehan (Villa Park). Coach: Mary Hauser (Mater Dei). 
</P>
<P>
 South -- Laura Czingula (Estancia), Sarah Davis (Tustin), Genevieve Evarts 
(Newport Harbor), Martita Emde (Marina), Karun Grossman (Dana Hills), Blythe 
Linsey (Calvary Chapel), Jamie Oenning (Woodbridge), Heather Robinson (Costa 
Mesa), Linda Rodriguez (La Quinta), Jennifer Stanley (University), Lisa 
Tamamasui (Westminster). Coach: Mary Mulligan (San Clemente). 
</P>
