<P>
TV RATINGS; CBS, 'HOME IMPROVEMENT' ARE SEASON'S CHAMPIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the final week of the so-called "official" prime-time season, "Home 
Improvement" and CBS finished right where they have been for most of the year: 
on top. "Home Improvement," the 3-year-old ABC sitcom starring Tim Allen and 
Patricia Richardson, was the week's and the season's most popular series, while 
CBS was the No. 1 network for the week and the season. 
</P>
<P>
 The prime-time season championship was CBS' third in a row. The network also 
won the season in daytime and late-night--the first time, CBS said, that a 
network had for the 30-week season, captured such a Triple Crown.  
</P>
<P>
 ABC finished second for the season and boasted that the performance of its new 
programs was the best of any network since 1979-80, with five new series among 
the Top 25: "Grace Under Fire," "NYPD Blue," "These Friends of Mine," "Thunder 
Alley" and "Turning Point." 
</P>
